A 17-year-old boy, Pinock Evans, who allegedly broke into a shop with the intent to steal, was yesterday brought before a Badagry Chief Magistrates’ Court. Evans pleaded not guilty. Prosecuting Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) Akpan Ikem said the defendant committed the offence on February 16, at about 5:40am at 1, Abule Era Road, Ijanikin, Lagos. He alleged that the defendant broke into Ocean of Life Pharmacy with intent to steal. “The defendant damaged three padlocks valued at N3,000, property of Mr. Okwuegbulem Promise. “Evans was arrested during the act and handed over to the police by the complainant,” Ikem said. Chief Magistrate Patrick Adekomaya remanded the defendant in a correction home at Adigbe in Abeokuta, Ogun State. The case continues on April 15.